1 
00:00:00,109 --> 00:00:04,560
I think we will lose this battle,
and a great many men will die.

2
00:00:04,875 --> 00:00:07,840
My God, Bolkonsky, what a shambles!

3
00:00:08,085 --> 00:00:09,550
[SHE SQUEALS]

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:11,110
How do you really feel about Sonya?

5
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:13,110
I do love her, Tasha.

6
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:14,345
[SHOUTS OF PAIN]

7
00:00:14,395 --> 00:00:16,840
I haven't been a very
affectionate husband...

8
00:00:17,386 --> 00:00:18,950
but it's no use saying that now.

9
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,000
[BABY CRIES]

10
00:00:21,152 --> 00:00:22,798
Here he is!

11
00:00:22,848 --> 00:00:25,520
Your wife is even more beautiful
than I remember, Bezukhov.

12
00:00:25,822 --> 00:00:28,478
To the health of beautiful women,
Petrushka -

13
00:00:28,689 --> 00:00:29,710
and their lovers.

14
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:31,600
I challenge you!

15
00:01:23,921 --> 00:01:25,241
Count Bezukhov?

16
00:01:29,068 --> 00:01:30,708
If I might...

17
00:01:32,095 --> 00:01:36,160
Look here, you don't want to be
fighting a duel with this fellow.

18
00:01:36,493 --> 00:01:39,195
Apologise,
say you lost your temper.

19
00:01:39,509 --> 00:01:40,750
No-one will think any
the worse of you.

20
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:41,790
No.

21
00:01:42,251 --> 00:01:44,480
No, we're here now. Just show
me where I have to go.

22
00:01:45,013 --> 00:01:47,720
- Captain Dolokhov?
- Let's get on with it, shall we?

23
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,240
If you could just remind me
how, um...

24
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:04,920
You point it, and...?

25
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,430
Oh, Lord.

26
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,524
Hold out your arm straight in front
of you, as steady as you can.

27
00:02:10,574 --> 00:02:13,266
And squeeze the trigger,
don't pull it.

28
00:02:13,316 --> 00:02:17,765
Turn sideways on - show him
your shoulder, not your chest.

29
00:02:17,815 --> 00:02:19,600
Don't give him an easy target.

30
00:02:20,026 --> 00:02:22,280
Thank you, I'd forgotten.
It's very kind of you.

31
00:02:22,807 --> 00:02:25,280
- There's still time to call it off.
- No.

32
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:29,000
No, I know it's stupid, but
I think I must go through with it.

33
00:02:31,850 --> 00:02:33,040
[GUN CLICKS]

34
00:02:34,954 --> 00:02:36,200
Good luck, then.

35
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:46,440
As the adversaries have refused
a reconciliation, we shall proceed.

36
00:02:47,772 --> 00:02:51,280
At the count of three, you may
advance towards each other.

37
00:02:51,391 --> 00:02:54,080
You may not go further than
the swords marking the barrier.

38
00:02:54,766 --> 00:02:58,920
After the count of three,
you may fire at any time.

39
00:03:10,823 --> 00:03:12,423
One.

40
00:03:14,033 --> 00:03:15,593
Two.

41
00:03:17,591 --> 00:03:18,751
Three.

42
00:03:31,050 --> 00:03:32,450
[GUNSHOT]

43
00:03:51,449 --> 00:03:52,830
- Fedya!
- Get back!

44
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:53,875
Dolokhov!

45
00:03:53,925 --> 00:03:58,240
No! Get back behind the barrier,
damn you!

46
00:03:59,473 --> 00:04:01,021
It's not over yet.

47
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:23,590
Turn! Cover yourself!

48
00:04:28,593 --> 00:04:30,233
[GUNSHOT]

49
00:04:31,945 --> 00:04:33,145
Missed!

50
00:04:37,719 --> 00:04:42,000
Stupid, stupid, stupid!

51
00:04:42,273 --> 00:04:44,753
Death, lies!

52
00:04:48,616 --> 00:04:50,176
How bad is it?

53
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,327
If she sees me dying,
it'll kill her.

54
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:55,357
Who?

55
00:04:55,407 --> 00:04:58,080
My mother. My angel.

56
00:04:58,493 --> 00:05:00,910
She and my poor sister,
they're the only good things

57
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,590
in my life, Rostov.

58
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:04,160
[HE GRUNTS]

59
00:05:04,274 --> 00:05:05,600
The only ones I care for.

60
00:05:08,574 --> 00:05:10,768
I have to live, for them.
You understand?

61
00:05:10,818 --> 00:05:12,270
Yes, I understand.

62
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,760
Move, man!

63
00:05:29,727 --> 00:05:32,760
Anatol, stop it.
You're not getting anything.

64
00:05:36,061 --> 00:05:37,870
Ah.

65
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,361
Pierre.

66
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,500
Well... I'll just...

67
00:05:53,781 --> 00:05:55,301
What have you done now?

68
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:58,933
What have I done?

69
00:06:00,339 --> 00:06:02,973
You've made an
exhibition of yourself,

70
00:06:03,023 --> 00:06:04,213
and of me.

71
00:06:05,013 --> 00:06:08,786
Someone told you that Dolokhov
was my lover, and you believed them.

72
00:06:09,278 --> 00:06:11,424
Now you've made us
the talk of all Moscow.

73
00:06:11,474 --> 00:06:13,866
Are you asking me to believe
that you're innocent?

74
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:16,218
Of course I am innocent!

75
00:06:16,268 --> 00:06:19,124
Though no-one would blame me
if I had taken a lover.

76
00:06:19,174 --> 00:06:22,275
It's not much fun being married to
a drunken oaf like you, you know.

77
00:06:22,517 --> 00:06:23,950
Most people think you're
half out of your wits.

78
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,280
- Don't speak to me like that!
- Why shouldn't I speak?

79
00:06:27,974 --> 00:06:30,406
I am the injured party here,
after all, not you.

80
00:06:32,603 --> 00:06:34,713
How am I to go into society
after all this?

81
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,280
I never interfered
with your pleasures.

82
00:06:41,694 --> 00:06:43,080
It's better that we part.

83
00:06:44,929 --> 00:06:45,887
What did you say?

84
00:06:45,937 --> 00:06:49,480
I said it's better that we part!
I'm leaving for Petersburg tomorrow.

85
00:06:52,552 --> 00:06:53,672
All right.

86
00:06:55,309 --> 00:06:56,989
If that's what you really want.

87
00:06:59,859 --> 00:07:02,462
You'll only expose yourself
to more ridicule.

88
00:07:02,512 --> 00:07:04,550
You know you'll have to give me
a fortune, don't you?

89
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,220
I'll kill you!

90
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:07,630
[HE HOWLS]

91
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:10,640
Out! Get out!

92
00:07:19,428 --> 00:07:21,268
[HE BREATHES HEAVILY]

93
00:07:54,164 --> 00:07:56,124
[DOOR OPENS]

94
00:07:59,999 --> 00:08:01,848
A thousand apologies,
Your Excellency,

95
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:05,558
there will be a little wait
for fresh horses.

96
00:08:05,608 --> 00:08:07,245
It's nice and warm in the parlour,

97
00:08:07,295 --> 00:08:09,310
if you don't mind sharing it
with another gentleman.

98
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,880
No, no - I don't suppose
I have any choice, do I?

99
00:08:21,150 --> 00:08:22,655
Good evening.

100
00:08:22,705 --> 00:08:24,040
Evening.

101
00:08:37,971 --> 00:08:39,080
[HE SIGHS]

102
00:08:46,090 --> 00:08:47,450
What?

103
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:53,840
I believe I have the pleasure
of speaking with Count Bezukhov?

104
00:08:56,483 --> 00:08:58,621
I have heard about the misfortune
that has befallen you, sir,

105
00:08:58,671 --> 00:09:00,440
and I am very sorry for it.

106
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:04,680
I should like to help you, if I can.

107
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:06,570
But if for any reason

108
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:09,560
you find conversation with me
unpleasant, please say so.

109
00:09:12,061 --> 00:09:13,372
No.

110
00:09:13,422 --> 00:09:15,311
No, I'm glad
to make your acquaintance.

111
00:09:15,361 --> 00:09:17,960
Then let me offer you
a brotherly handshake.

112
00:09:22,782 --> 00:09:24,190
You're a Mason?

113
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,556
Yes,

114
00:09:25,712 --> 00:09:28,140
I belong to the brotherhood
of Freemasons.

115
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:32,520
I'm afraid my way of thinking
is very different from yours.

116
00:09:34,186 --> 00:09:35,650
I don't believe in God.

117
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,291
Of course you don't.

118
00:09:37,341 --> 00:09:40,040
You don't believe in God
because you don't know him.

119
00:09:40,622 --> 00:09:42,360
And that's why you're so unhappy.

120
00:09:42,778 --> 00:09:44,465
I am unhappy.

121
00:09:45,366 --> 00:09:49,060
I should think anyone could see that,
but what am I to do about it?

122
00:09:49,451 --> 00:09:51,720
How can I know God,

123
00:09:52,506 --> 00:09:56,393
if all my powers of reasoning
tell me he cannot exist?

124
00:09:56,443 --> 00:09:59,720
God is not apprehended by reason,
my son,

125
00:10:00,103 --> 00:10:01,143
but by life.

126
00:10:02,628 --> 00:10:04,108
I don't understand you, sir.

127
00:10:05,147 --> 00:10:06,307
Well...

128
00:10:08,186 --> 00:10:12,720
..you are young, you are rich,
you are educated.

129
00:10:13,343 --> 00:10:14,770
What have you done with

130
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:17,400
all these good things
that have been given you?

131
00:10:18,884 --> 00:10:20,164
Very little, so far.

132
00:10:21,506 --> 00:10:25,746
You need to purify yourself,
listen to your conscience.

133
00:10:26,673 --> 00:10:28,513
Look at yourself.

134
00:10:28,563 --> 00:10:30,425
Ask yourself,

135
00:10:30,475 --> 00:10:33,248
are you content with yourself?

136
00:10:33,298 --> 00:10:34,545
With your life?

137
00:10:37,185 --> 00:10:39,360
No, I hate my life.

138
00:10:40,304 --> 00:10:42,348
I hate myself.

139
00:10:42,398 --> 00:10:43,960
Good.

140
00:10:44,481 --> 00:10:46,120
You have taken the first step.

141
00:10:57,400 --> 00:11:00,040
[RECITES BAPTISM CEREMONY]

142
00:11:10,707 --> 00:11:12,187
[BABY CRIES]

143
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:29,280
Your wound still troubles you?

144
00:11:29,825 --> 00:11:31,320
Yes, a little.

145
00:11:31,887 --> 00:11:34,347
- You still keep up a good pace, Father.
- Why would I not?

146
00:11:34,668 --> 00:11:36,282
I never vary!

147
00:11:36,332 --> 00:11:39,760
Work, exercise, a good night's
sleep - that's all a man needs.

148
00:11:41,330 --> 00:11:44,587
What next for you?
Back to the army?

149
00:11:44,861 --> 00:11:46,181
No.

150
00:11:46,666 --> 00:11:48,800
I've had enough for now
of dreams of glory.

151
00:11:49,008 --> 00:11:51,725
And Napoleon's wars seem like
nothing to do with us.

152
00:11:51,775 --> 00:11:55,600
- I'd like to make myself useful here.
- Good! Glad to hear it.

153
00:11:55,650 --> 00:11:57,863
Plenty here to keep you occupied.

154
00:11:57,913 --> 00:12:00,880
Build yourself a house
on the Bogucharovo estate.

155
00:12:01,413 --> 00:12:03,160
A man needs his own place.

156
00:12:03,210 --> 00:12:04,965
What do you say to that?

157
00:12:05,015 --> 00:12:07,560
- I think it's an excellent idea.
- Good!

158
00:12:09,421 --> 00:12:11,061
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

159
00:12:17,012 --> 00:12:18,418
I've drawn up a list of economies

160
00:12:18,468 --> 00:12:20,035
I strongly recommend
to Your Excellency.

161
00:12:20,085 --> 00:12:22,325
Yes, yes, but one doesn't care
to penny-pinch.

162
00:12:22,375 --> 00:12:24,710
One has to entertain
the odd guest now and then.

163
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:28,440
- The position is really quite serious.
- All right, all right,

164
00:12:28,594 --> 00:12:31,334
austerity shall be our watchword
from now on, thank you.

165
00:12:31,384 --> 00:12:34,300
Thank you for your
meticulous accounting.

166
00:12:35,291 --> 00:12:38,323
- I'll be good, I promise.
- Your Excellency.

167
00:12:38,373 --> 00:12:39,972
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

168
00:12:41,203 --> 00:12:44,832
Well, what is it, my dear boy,
as if I couldn't guess?

169
00:12:44,882 --> 00:12:48,153
I'm sorry to have to ask, Father,
but I do find myself a little short.

170
00:12:48,203 --> 00:12:50,435
I've been helping Dolokhov
with his medical expenses, you see.

171
00:12:50,485 --> 00:12:53,591
- Ah, yes, how is the poor fellow?
- Oh, he's very much better.

172
00:12:53,641 --> 00:12:57,059
But he and his mother and sister,
they live in such a poor way, they can

173
00:12:57,109 --> 00:13:00,830
- barely afford to heat their rooms.
- And you've been helping them.

174
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:03,043
You're a generous-hearted boy.

175
00:13:03,093 --> 00:13:06,150
Now, I can't spare you very much
just at the moment.

176
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:08,590
Bakshin was very strict with me
just now.

177
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:11,030
Will 2,000 roubles
be sufficient for your needs?

178
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:13,270
That will be ample, Father -
you're very good.

179
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:15,847
See if you can make it last
till Spring.

180
00:13:15,897 --> 00:13:17,600
I give you my word that it will.

181
00:13:18,183 --> 00:13:20,804
And, Father, I should like to
invite Dolokhov

182
00:13:20,854 --> 00:13:23,577
to come and stay here for
a little while. May I do that?

183
00:13:23,627 --> 00:13:26,695
My dear boy, any friend
of yours is welcome here!

184
00:13:26,745 --> 00:13:27,853
Thank you.

185
00:13:31,502 --> 00:13:32,822
[HE SIGHS]

186
00:13:34,705 --> 00:13:37,006
To the health and happiness of all,

187
00:13:37,056 --> 00:13:39,681
and the splendid recovery
of our young friend here!

188
00:13:39,731 --> 00:13:41,321
I can't thank you enough,
Count Rostov,

189
00:13:41,371 --> 00:13:43,384
and you, Countess,
for your kindness to me.

190
00:13:43,434 --> 00:13:45,360
Nonsense - it's our pleasure.

191
00:13:45,410 --> 00:13:47,245
You're one of the heroes
of Austerlitz.

192
00:13:47,295 --> 00:13:49,630
Nothing to be proud of, sir -
I'm just a man who loves to fight.

193
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:51,269
It's all I know, to my shame.

194
00:13:51,319 --> 00:13:55,137
Don't disparage yourself, Fedya -
none of us will believe it anyway.

195
00:13:55,187 --> 00:13:58,080
Then I'd better say nothing
about myself at all.

196
00:14:01,178 --> 00:14:03,920
How is your mazurka coming along,
Natasha?

197
00:14:05,702 --> 00:14:09,002
Well, we thought we were
doing very well, until

198
00:14:09,052 --> 00:14:11,183
until Denisov told us
we were doing it all wrong.

199
00:14:11,530 --> 00:14:13,290
[LAUGHTER]

200
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:16,030
- You did.
- What do you know about it, Denisov?

201
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:18,030
Oh, I was dancing
the mazurka in Poland

202
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,117
when you were still in
petticoats, my boy!

203
00:14:20,167 --> 00:14:21,189
Really?

204
00:14:22,587 --> 00:14:24,655
The way they used to teach us
in Poland...

205
00:14:24,705 --> 00:14:27,357
Have you always lived with
the family, Sonya?

206
00:14:27,407 --> 00:14:29,787
Yes, since I was a little girl.

207
00:14:30,598 --> 00:14:32,619
Nikolai speaks so warmly of you,

208
00:14:32,669 --> 00:14:34,196
and now I can see why.

209
00:14:35,473 --> 00:14:36,947
I should like to know you better,
Sonya.

210
00:14:36,997 --> 00:14:39,237
DENISOV: ..It was the footman!

211
00:14:40,898 --> 00:14:43,952
Dolokhov watches you all the time.

212
00:14:44,312 --> 00:14:47,039
Doesn't it make you
feel uncomfortable?

213
00:14:47,089 --> 00:14:48,398
Yes.

214
00:14:49,194 --> 00:14:50,900
But there's no harm in it.

215
00:14:51,896 --> 00:14:55,331
He can look all he likes.
It won't change anything.

216
00:14:55,381 --> 00:14:57,113
You're so sure of yourself.

217
00:14:58,515 --> 00:15:01,320
Mama says that girls
are like mayflies.

218
00:15:01,746 --> 00:15:04,524
That they have their day in the sun,
and then it's over.

219
00:15:04,574 --> 00:15:06,571
It's more than a day.

220
00:15:06,621 --> 00:15:09,641
But how long? A year or two?

221
00:15:09,691 --> 00:15:12,369
To choose or be chosen. And then,

222
00:15:13,260 --> 00:15:17,377
and then, that's our lives settled...
for ever.

223
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:19,397
It's frightening.

224
00:15:19,447 --> 00:15:22,120
You just have to choose right,
that's all.

225
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:24,320
But how will I know?

226
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:26,240
You will.

227
00:15:26,673 --> 00:15:27,760
But will I?

228
00:15:31,236 --> 00:15:33,531
I'm sorry, Nikki,
I just don't like him.

229
00:15:33,581 --> 00:15:35,850
Why on Earth not?
Everyone else does.

230
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:39,042
- There's something cruel about him.
- Now you're just being ridiculous.

231
00:15:39,092 --> 00:15:42,363
- No, I'm not!
- He's the kindest, gentlest...

232
00:15:42,413 --> 00:15:44,855
If you could see him at home
with his mother and sister...

233
00:15:44,905 --> 00:15:48,405
Well, I don't know about that.
All I know is what I feel.

234
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:52,870
And I'm sure Pierre was in the right
when he challenged him.

235
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:54,830
Oh, Pierre! He's an idiot.

236
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,440
No, he's not.
I'd trust him with my life.

237
00:15:57,892 --> 00:15:59,492
Whereas, that one...

238
00:16:00,610 --> 00:16:03,160
..can't you see
he's trying to take Sonya from you?

239
00:16:04,214 --> 00:16:06,672
He's just being nice to her.
He likes you, too.

240
00:16:06,722 --> 00:16:08,003
No, he doesn't.

241
00:16:09,222 --> 00:16:13,240
And I'm not sure
he likes you, either - not really.

242
00:16:13,496 --> 00:16:15,160
[HE SNORTS]

243
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:24,533
[SWORDS CLASH]

244
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,360
You sure you're up to this, Fedya?

245
00:16:35,718 --> 00:16:37,118
Come again.

246
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:48,920
Whoa!

247
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:54,498
You'll have to show me
how to do that one!

248
00:16:55,611 --> 00:16:57,251
Trade secret, my boy.

249
00:16:59,864 --> 00:17:00,884
[WATER SPLASHING]

250
00:17:00,934 --> 00:17:03,320
Your cousin is a lovely girl,
Rostov.

251
00:17:04,429 --> 00:17:06,032
And your sister, of course.

252
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:09,349
I thought you were the man
that despised all women,

253
00:17:09,399 --> 00:17:13,080
- except his own mother and sister.
- I changed my mind, very recently.

254
00:17:13,643 --> 00:17:16,002
Innocence and purity
are very rare.

255
00:17:17,444 --> 00:17:19,030
You've known these girls
all your life,

256
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:21,440
you take their qualities
for granted.

257
00:17:21,885 --> 00:17:24,405
I suppose you're right.
I've never really thought about it.

258
00:17:25,696 --> 00:17:28,545
You see and feel very deeply,
don't you, Dolokhov?

259
00:17:28,595 --> 00:17:29,840
Some things.

260
00:17:32,047 --> 00:17:33,447
Some things.

261
00:17:36,036 --> 00:17:37,338
A-ha!

262
00:17:37,947 --> 00:17:39,413
- A mazurka!
- A-ha!

263
00:17:39,463 --> 00:17:42,790
I knew we had one somewhere!
Come on, Denisov.

264
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:45,509
We've heard you boasting,
now you can show us what you can do!

265
00:17:45,559 --> 00:17:46,750
- No, no, no.
- Yes!

266
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:47,751
Make him, Father!

267
00:17:47,801 --> 00:17:49,908
No excuse, Denisov,
you might as well submit.

268
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:52,600
- Yes, best idea all night.
- Oh, no!

269
00:17:52,951 --> 00:17:54,591
[SHE LAUGHS]

270
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,040
[MUSIC STARTS]

271
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:46,997
[SHE SQUEALS]

272
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,040
[APPLAUSE]

273
00:18:57,090 --> 00:19:01,334
Denisov, you're a wonderful
dancer! I had no idea.

274
00:19:01,384 --> 00:19:03,830
For you - all for you.

275
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,484
Oh, thank you.

276
00:19:05,534 --> 00:19:06,890
Now this, you absolutely deserve!

277
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:08,163
- Yes!
- Thank you.

278
00:19:08,213 --> 00:19:10,200
Shall we sit down?

279
00:19:13,704 --> 00:19:15,464
[PIANO PLAYS]

280
00:19:18,237 --> 00:19:20,877
[HE SINGS IN RUSSIAN]

281
00:19:22,558 --> 00:19:23,938
Countess.

282
00:19:25,925 --> 00:19:27,289
Natasha.

283
00:19:27,339 --> 00:19:29,680
If I don't speak now,
I'm afraid I never will.

284
00:19:32,142 --> 00:19:33,422
I adore you.

285
00:19:34,581 --> 00:19:37,187
I have never felt this way
about any woman or girl.

286
00:19:37,237 --> 00:19:40,231
I think about you all day
and dream of you at night.

287
00:19:40,281 --> 00:19:42,974
- Oh, dear.
- I know I have no hope,

288
00:19:43,475 --> 00:19:44,920
but I must ask you.

289
00:19:45,195 --> 00:19:46,950
Will you make me
the happiest man on earth

290
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,760
and consent to be my wife?

291
00:19:50,435 --> 00:19:52,420
Oh... er...

292
00:19:54,972 --> 00:19:56,632
I wish you hadn't said that.

293
00:19:57,915 --> 00:19:58,915
I beg your pardon.

294
00:20:00,090 --> 00:20:02,560
- I couldn't help it.
- Dear Denisov.

295
00:20:03,035 --> 00:20:05,550
I'm so fond of you...

296
00:20:06,902 --> 00:20:09,081
I can't say it.

297
00:20:11,202 --> 00:20:12,760
Please.

298
00:20:13,163 --> 00:20:14,580
Forget about it.

299
00:20:15,074 --> 00:20:16,633
A moment of madness.

300
00:20:18,124 --> 00:20:19,564
All over now.

301
00:20:24,209 --> 00:20:26,249
Now, if you will excuse me...

302
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:30,160
[CONTINUES SINGING]

303
00:20:56,083 --> 00:20:57,683
[DOOR OPENS]

304
00:20:58,508 --> 00:21:00,108
Now you must be blindfolded.

305
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,706
Why is that?

306
00:21:05,308 --> 00:21:07,086
If you wish to join our brotherhood,

307
00:21:07,136 --> 00:21:10,240
you must be willing to submit
to our rituals without question.

308
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,720
Are you willing?

309
00:21:15,822 --> 00:21:17,302
Yes.

310
00:21:18,425 --> 00:21:19,665
Yes.

311
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:29,720
I will leave you now.

312
00:21:31,387 --> 00:21:33,618
When you hear knocking,

313
00:21:33,668 --> 00:21:35,868
you may remove the blindfold.

314
00:21:37,042 --> 00:21:38,682
[RECEDING FOOTSTEPS]

315
00:21:53,074 --> 00:21:54,554
[LOUD BANGING]

316
00:21:58,756 --> 00:22:01,316
Why have you come here?

317
00:22:01,634 --> 00:22:03,103
For wisdom?

318
00:22:03,153 --> 00:22:04,953
For virtue?

319
00:22:05,172 --> 00:22:06,972
For enlightenment?

320
00:22:08,331 --> 00:22:09,651
For renewal.

321
00:22:10,998 --> 00:22:12,198
I want renewal.

322
00:22:13,144 --> 00:22:16,504
MEN: Sic transit gloria mundi!

323
00:22:16,923 --> 00:22:19,703
Always aid your brother man.

324
00:22:20,042 --> 00:22:22,300
Raise up the fallen.

325
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:24,359
Forgive your enemy.

326
00:22:24,635 --> 00:22:28,480
Take no revenge upon him,
unless it be but to do him good.

327
00:22:29,245 --> 00:22:32,020
Go out into the world now.

328
00:22:32,763 --> 00:22:37,400
Live not for yourself,
but for others.

329
00:22:39,657 --> 00:22:44,537
You must be so happy that he has
decided to turn his back on society.

330
00:22:44,587 --> 00:22:47,398
Well, I won't say a word against
my husband, Anna Pavlovna,

331
00:22:47,448 --> 00:22:50,780
but truly it has been a bit
of a trial the last few months.

332
00:22:50,830 --> 00:22:53,288
I'm very glad to be back
in Petersburg.

333
00:22:53,338 --> 00:22:57,915
And the Emperor himself has taken
an interest in your affairs, I hear.

334
00:22:57,965 --> 00:23:00,994
Yes, he's been kind.
More than kind, really.

335
00:23:01,044 --> 00:23:02,185
Vraiment?

336
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:05,146
All the old crowd here, I see.

337
00:23:05,904 --> 00:23:07,312
Bilibin!

338
00:23:07,818 --> 00:23:09,705
Enchanting as ever, Comtesse.

339
00:23:09,755 --> 00:23:14,040
Well, I should hope so. But tell me,
who is that young man over there?

340
00:23:14,731 --> 00:23:16,513
Ah. Boris Drubestkoy.

341
00:23:16,778 --> 00:23:18,602
A very promising young man.

342
00:23:18,652 --> 00:23:21,610
Since Austerlitz, he's been
attached to the Prussian staff.

343
00:23:21,660 --> 00:23:23,313
Our oldest allies.

344
00:23:23,363 --> 00:23:26,649
They've only betrayed us four times
in the last three years,

345
00:23:26,699 --> 00:23:29,219
but now they're supposed to be
the solution to the eternal...

346
00:23:29,269 --> 00:23:32,515
Stop talking politics to me,
Bilibin, I can't bear it.

347
00:23:32,565 --> 00:23:34,188
Just introduce me
to your little friend

348
00:23:34,238 --> 00:23:36,560
and make yourself scarce, hmm?

349
00:23:37,362 --> 00:23:38,498
Drubetskoy?

350
00:23:38,548 --> 00:23:39,788
Over here.

351
00:23:40,511 --> 00:23:44,007
Countess Bezukhova,
may I present Boris Drubetskoy,

352
00:23:44,057 --> 00:23:46,812
one of our most promising
young diplomats?

353
00:23:46,862 --> 00:23:47,790
Enchante.

354
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:49,516
And you're with the Prussian
High Command?

355
00:23:49,566 --> 00:23:52,687
How exciting, to be so close
to all the decision-makers.

356
00:23:52,737 --> 00:23:54,110
Do tell me about it.

357
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:57,043
Are you interested in politics,
Countess Bezukhova?

358
00:23:57,093 --> 00:23:58,573
I adore politics.

359
00:24:00,155 --> 00:24:02,195
It's all so fascinating!

360
00:24:03,713 --> 00:24:06,830
Ah, Dolokhov, you'll never guess
who I just ran into!

361
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,280
Dolokhov?

362
00:24:08,558 --> 00:24:10,289
What's the matter?
What's going on?

363
00:24:10,339 --> 00:24:11,173
Did he tell you?

364
00:24:11,223 --> 00:24:12,748
No, he told me nothing.
What's this all about?

365
00:24:12,798 --> 00:24:14,270
There's been a bit of a scene.

366
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,360
He's proposed to Sonya
and she refused him.

367
00:24:16,410 --> 00:24:18,001
She told him she was in love
with someone else.

368
00:24:18,051 --> 00:24:20,230
You, of course,
though she didn't say so.

369
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:23,461
- He actually proposed to her?
- Yes! Couldn't you see it coming?

370
00:24:23,511 --> 00:24:26,123
Sometimes I don't think
you see anything.

371
00:24:26,173 --> 00:24:28,164
Mamma's not pleased.

372
00:24:28,214 --> 00:24:30,039
She told Sonya that Dolokhov's
a very good match

373
00:24:30,089 --> 00:24:32,722
for a girl with no prospects.
But I'm glad she refused him.

374
00:24:32,772 --> 00:24:35,246
- Aren't you?
- Yes, yes, of course I am.

375
00:24:35,296 --> 00:24:36,923
But I should talk to her about it.

376
00:24:36,973 --> 00:24:38,673
Yes, I'll get her to come down.

377
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:56,667
So, he really proposed to you?

378
00:24:56,717 --> 00:24:57,971
Yes.

379
00:24:58,021 --> 00:25:00,000
I didn't want him to.

380
00:25:01,085 --> 00:25:04,191
You know, as Mamma said,
it would be a good match for you.

381
00:25:04,241 --> 00:25:06,430
He's such a good fellow
and a dear friend.

382
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,829
I'd hate for you to feel as though
you'd missed an opportunity.

383
00:25:08,879 --> 00:25:11,053
Well, I've already refused him.

384
00:25:11,281 --> 00:25:13,587
And nothing could make me
change my mind.

385
00:25:14,311 --> 00:25:16,261
He's been very kind to me,
but I could never love him,

386
00:25:16,311 --> 00:25:18,170
- and I told him so.
- Sonya, if you've refused him for my sake,

387
00:25:18,220 --> 00:25:19,334
- No, don't say that to me!
- then I'm afraid...

388
00:25:19,384 --> 00:25:21,544
No, but I must tell you
the whole truth. Look.

389
00:25:22,317 --> 00:25:23,504
I love you,

390
00:25:24,012 --> 00:25:25,759
I think, more than anyone
I've ever known.

391
00:25:25,809 --> 00:25:26,938
Well, that's enough for me.

392
00:25:26,988 --> 00:25:30,828
Yes, but I've fallen in love before
and I expect that I will again.

393
00:25:30,878 --> 00:25:33,058
I can't help it, it's the way I am.

394
00:25:33,858 --> 00:25:37,298
And then when Mamma
refuses to give her consent,

395
00:25:37,792 --> 00:25:41,392
you see, I'm not in a position
to promise you anything.

396
00:25:41,592 --> 00:25:44,212
- I don't ask you to, I never have.
- Yes, but I think you should consider

397
00:25:44,262 --> 00:25:45,862
Dolokhov's proposal.

398
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:50,760
I'd rather not marry at all
than marry him.

399
00:25:52,288 --> 00:25:55,128
I love you and I always will.

400
00:25:55,617 --> 00:26:01,560
But I don't ask anything of you.
I don't expect anything more.

401
00:26:03,959 --> 00:26:05,519
I don't deserve you.

402
00:26:08,079 --> 00:26:09,519
You're an angel.

403
00:26:21,795 --> 00:26:23,465
[HE SIGHS]

404
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:26,915
Good day, good day, I've come
to see how you're all getting along.

405
00:26:29,694 --> 00:26:31,933
These cottages
look very bad, Grigori.

406
00:26:31,983 --> 00:26:34,004
They need new roofs,
at the very least.

407
00:26:34,054 --> 00:26:36,630
Yes, indeed, your Excellency.
See you make a note of that.

408
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:39,350
And here would be a good place
for a school.

409
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,670
A school, your Excellency?

410
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,960
Yes, indeed. Every boy
should have the chance

411
00:26:43,010 --> 00:26:45,648
to learn to read and write.
And the girls, too.

412
00:26:45,698 --> 00:26:48,590
But where will the teacher
come from, your Excellency?

413
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:51,194
Oh, there are teachers
everywhere. Just

414
00:26:51,244 --> 00:26:53,980
build the school
and the teachers will come!

415
00:26:54,327 --> 00:26:56,487
Now! Grain stores.

416
00:26:59,508 --> 00:27:00,748
Hello.

417
00:27:06,371 --> 00:27:07,891
Grain stores.

418
00:27:09,196 --> 00:27:11,796
[CLOCK BELLS RING]

419
00:27:14,251 --> 00:27:16,211
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

420
00:27:16,367 --> 00:27:17,767
Oh, it's you.

421
00:27:20,226 --> 00:27:22,341
I'm so sorry, but

422
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:25,313
did I mistake the day?
Or the time?

423
00:27:26,452 --> 00:27:28,292
No, I don't think so.

424
00:27:28,777 --> 00:27:32,737
It's just... where is everybody?

425
00:27:33,954 --> 00:27:36,074
Don't you think
there are enough of us?

426
00:27:36,613 --> 00:27:39,813
Well, yes, of course.

427
00:27:41,223 --> 00:27:43,643
What did you think
all this was about?

428
00:27:45,512 --> 00:27:46,892
Well...

429
00:27:49,094 --> 00:27:50,254
Are you hungry?

430
00:27:51,324 --> 00:27:52,524
 Um...

431
00:27:54,112 --> 00:27:55,445
not particularly.

432
00:27:58,560 --> 00:27:59,960
Come on, then.

433
00:28:41,217 --> 00:28:43,128
All right, gentlemen, who's in?

434
00:28:43,178 --> 00:28:46,331
Ah, Rostov! The very man!

435
00:28:46,381 --> 00:28:49,179
Thank you for inviting me, Dolokhov.
You've been a stranger lately.

436
00:28:49,229 --> 00:28:51,025
I've been busy.

437
00:28:51,557 --> 00:28:54,680
But you're still my... I mean,
everything's all right between us?

438
00:28:54,730 --> 00:28:57,543
Why wouldn't it be?
Why don't you join us at the table?

439
00:28:57,593 --> 00:28:59,630
Or are you afraid
of playing with me?

440
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:02,270
[HE LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]
I haven't any money with me.

441
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:04,239
That's all right, I trust you.

442
00:29:04,289 --> 00:29:05,789
Play or not,
it's all the same to me.

443
00:29:05,839 --> 00:29:07,890
But I tell you,
if you play with me, you'll lose.

444
00:29:07,940 --> 00:29:09,390
ALL: Ooh!

445
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:11,161
Well, you don't know that.

446
00:29:11,211 --> 00:29:12,920
You know what they say about me?

447
00:29:12,970 --> 00:29:14,820
Dolokhov makes his own luck.

448
00:29:17,905 --> 00:29:18,809
I'll play.

449
00:29:18,859 --> 00:29:21,007
Good man!
Make some room for him.

450
00:29:22,721 --> 00:29:24,481
Stake your bets, gentlemen.

451
00:29:27,177 --> 00:29:28,937
Five roubles on the five.

452
00:29:30,315 --> 00:29:31,995
Three of hearts the soda.

453
00:29:32,472 --> 00:29:33,872
Ten wins.

454
00:29:34,670 --> 00:29:36,110
And five loses.

455
00:29:36,385 --> 00:29:39,080
All right, Rostov,
I'm keeping tally.

456
00:29:39,502 --> 00:29:41,302
Stake your bets, gentlemen.

457
00:29:43,078 --> 00:29:44,518
Ten on the ace.

458
00:29:47,547 --> 00:29:49,027
Any more?

459
00:29:50,447 --> 00:29:51,910
All right.

460
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,080
Seven...

461
00:29:53,438 --> 00:29:54,838
King...

462
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,670
..and ace loses.

463
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:58,950
Bad luck, Rostov.

464
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:02,440
Maybe it's not your night.
Stake your bets, gentlemen.

465
00:30:04,173 --> 00:30:05,213
20 on the seven.

466
00:30:14,465 --> 00:30:16,025
[AUDIENCE GROANS]

467
00:30:17,627 --> 00:30:19,827
That's how it goes sometimes.

468
00:30:20,931 --> 00:30:22,971
Perhaps you'd like to quit, Rostov?

469
00:30:29,402 --> 00:30:30,722
40 on the King.

470
00:30:33,057 --> 00:30:34,657
Place your bets.

471
00:30:36,164 --> 00:30:38,924
- 1,000 on the ace.
- Any more?

472
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:42,108
Jack of diamonds.

473
00:30:42,158 --> 00:30:43,955
Three of spades.

474
00:30:44,234 --> 00:30:45,754
Ace of diamonds.

475
00:30:49,034 --> 00:30:51,114
So, how much do I owe you now?

476
00:30:54,652 --> 00:30:56,852
[CHICKENS SQUAWK]

477
00:31:01,554 --> 00:31:03,194
[PIGS GRUNT]

478
00:31:08,504 --> 00:31:11,144
[NATASHA SINGS]

479
00:31:21,981 --> 00:31:24,021
[NIKOLAI HUMS ALONG]

480
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:37,920
[HE SINGS]

481
00:31:43,897 --> 00:31:45,697
[BOTH SING]

482
00:32:18,637 --> 00:32:20,388
[SONYA CLAPS]

483
00:32:20,438 --> 00:32:24,120
You have a lovely voice, Nikki -
we should sing together more often!

484
00:32:25,538 --> 00:32:27,298
I have to go and speak to Father.

485
00:32:32,158 --> 00:32:34,920
[KNOCK AT DOOR]
Ah, the night bird!

486
00:32:34,970 --> 00:32:38,200
Home at last!
Well, did you have a good time?

487
00:32:38,588 --> 00:32:40,160
Not especially.

488
00:32:40,812 --> 00:32:42,891
Father, I'm afraid I'm going to
need some more money.

489
00:32:42,941 --> 00:32:44,030
Already?

490
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:45,265
I had a feeling
it wouldn't last you,

491
00:32:45,315 --> 00:32:47,691
but I didn't think
it would be so soon!

492
00:32:47,741 --> 00:32:51,741
Well, you're only young once.
How much do you need, my boy?

493
00:32:52,171 --> 00:32:53,931
Well, it's rather a lot.

494
00:32:54,267 --> 00:32:57,627
Um, I lost a bit at cards,
you see and...

495
00:32:58,449 --> 00:33:00,274
That is, a good deal,
a very great deal actually.

496
00:33:00,324 --> 00:33:02,386
- How much?
- 43,000.

497
00:33:03,243 --> 00:33:04,723
What?

498
00:33:06,474 --> 00:33:07,914
To whom?

499
00:33:08,431 --> 00:33:10,911
43,000?! Are you joking?

500
00:33:11,370 --> 00:33:13,170
And I promised to pay tomorrow.

501
00:33:17,310 --> 00:33:18,710
Tomorrow.

502
00:33:19,593 --> 00:33:21,833
I suppose it happens
to everyone, at some point.

503
00:33:22,841 --> 00:33:24,281
Yes.

504
00:33:25,668 --> 00:33:27,508
Yes, I suppose
these things do happen.

505
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:30,560
It's a little difficult.

506
00:33:32,349 --> 00:33:35,869
We shall have to close up the
Moscow house and go to Otradnoe.

507
00:33:36,143 --> 00:33:37,263
Well...

508
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:42,050
Well, it can't be helped.

509
00:33:42,100 --> 00:33:43,540
Can't be helped.

510
00:33:44,903 --> 00:33:47,612
Oh, Papa! Please forgive me -
I'm so sorry!

511
00:33:47,662 --> 00:33:50,311
Forgive me,
I'm sorry... I didn't mean..

512
00:33:50,361 --> 00:33:51,761
There, there.

513
00:33:52,485 --> 00:33:53,885
There, there.

514
00:33:59,899 --> 00:34:01,499
Well, here we are.

515
00:34:03,181 --> 00:34:06,200
We didn't exactly enhance
our reputations on leave, did we?

516
00:34:06,824 --> 00:34:08,855
I certainly didn't.

517
00:34:08,905 --> 00:34:12,065
When the leave's too long,
the soldier goes wrong.

518
00:34:12,761 --> 00:34:15,960
At least we know what
we have to do now - kill Frenchmen.

519
00:34:16,249 --> 00:34:17,849
We can do that.

520
00:34:19,680 --> 00:34:22,590
By the order
of the Emperor Alexander,

521
00:34:22,640 --> 00:34:24,600
and by the grace of God,

522
00:34:25,110 --> 00:34:27,510
it is announced that a peace treaty

523
00:34:27,560 --> 00:34:31,200
has been ratified
with the Emperor of France,

524
00:34:31,684 --> 00:34:35,030
who will now be our gallant ally.

525
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,840
[HUBBUB]

526
00:34:37,184 --> 00:34:41,560
The Emperor Napoleon has been
awarded the Order of St Andrew,

527
00:34:41,937 --> 00:34:46,860
as a mark
of our nations' amity and accord.

528
00:34:47,766 --> 00:34:49,286
Thank you.

529
00:34:51,793 --> 00:34:53,571
Oh, excellent.

530
00:34:53,621 --> 00:34:54,910
What was that all about?

531
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:57,950
The usual thing.
We've changed sides.

532
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,590
Our enemies are our friends now.

533
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:03,057
- So we're friends with the French?
- I know, I know.

534
00:35:03,107 --> 00:35:06,120
It's a mad world.
No use trying to understand.

535
00:35:13,407 --> 00:35:14,847
[HE GRUNTS]

536
00:35:21,389 --> 00:35:23,309
[BUZZING]

537
00:35:23,691 --> 00:35:25,651
[WATER PATTERS]

538
00:35:26,691 --> 00:35:28,091
[BIRDS CALL]

539
00:35:32,563 --> 00:35:34,723
[ICE CRACKLES]

540
00:36:10,578 --> 00:36:12,218
[HORSES' HOOVES]

541
00:36:21,238 --> 00:36:23,814
Is Prince Andrei at home?
I'm an old friend.

542
00:36:23,864 --> 00:36:27,020
Yes, your Excellency.
Shall I tell him you're here?

543
00:36:27,070 --> 00:36:29,110
No, no, let me surprise him.

544
00:36:42,731 --> 00:36:44,531
Pierre!

545
00:36:45,094 --> 00:36:46,480
How unexpected!

546
00:36:48,471 --> 00:36:51,624
I'm delighted to see you!
What brings you to these parts?

547
00:36:51,674 --> 00:36:53,310
I've been making
a tour of my estates,

548
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,657
trying to make
conditions better for my serfs

549
00:36:55,707 --> 00:36:58,940
and my tenant farmers, make my farms
more efficient, and so on.

550
00:36:59,996 --> 00:37:02,955
Really, I've no idea what I'm doing.

551
00:37:03,005 --> 00:37:06,310
How are you? I've been
thinking about you so much,

552
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:08,000
wondering what you've been up to!

553
00:37:09,250 --> 00:37:11,210
Not very much, is the short answer.

554
00:37:12,356 --> 00:37:15,796
Come, let's have something
to eat and drink.

555
00:37:16,442 --> 00:37:19,390
Yes, this is the life -
bread and cheese,

556
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:21,480
and wine, in moderation.

557
00:37:21,870 --> 00:37:23,590
To hell with high society!

558
00:37:24,930 --> 00:37:28,690
You know, you're exactly the same.
You haven't changed a bit!

559
00:37:29,754 --> 00:37:31,474
Do you think so?

560
00:37:32,005 --> 00:37:36,100
In myself, I believe I've changed
a great deal - and for the better.

561
00:37:38,387 --> 00:37:40,427
I heard about your marriage.

562
00:37:41,018 --> 00:37:42,818
And how it ended?

563
00:37:43,513 --> 00:37:45,553
You heard about the duel?

564
00:37:45,655 --> 00:37:48,535
Yes, you had
to go through that, too.

565
00:37:49,056 --> 00:37:51,970
The one thing I thank God for
is that I didn't kill that man.

566
00:37:52,020 --> 00:37:54,491
Why so? If a dog is vicious,
he's better off dead.

567
00:37:54,541 --> 00:37:57,238
But to take a man's life,
that must always be wrong.

568
00:37:57,288 --> 00:38:00,408
Why must it always be wrong?
For you, perhaps.

569
00:38:01,076 --> 00:38:04,640
For me, there are only two evils -

570
00:38:05,327 --> 00:38:07,777
sickness and remorse.

571
00:38:09,581 --> 00:38:13,581
Since Lise died,
I have been wracked with remorse.

572
00:38:16,898 --> 00:38:19,298
I treated her unkindly
and now she's gone.

573
00:38:20,899 --> 00:38:22,539
Disappeared into nowhere.

574
00:38:24,194 --> 00:38:26,034
No way for me to make amends.

575
00:38:31,358 --> 00:38:35,298
I've been staring
into the abyss, Pierre.

576
00:38:38,569 --> 00:38:42,169
So now, my sole aim
is to live for myself.

577
00:38:42,597 --> 00:38:43,946
To do as little harm as possible

578
00:38:43,996 --> 00:38:46,070
and to have as little to do
with other people as I can.

579
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:48,800
No, I can't agree.
That wouldn't be enough.

580
00:38:49,394 --> 00:38:52,867
I used to live for myself
and I ruined my life.

581
00:38:52,917 --> 00:38:56,390
Now, I try to think of others,
actively try to help them,

582
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:58,600
and I'm much happier for it.

583
00:38:58,968 --> 00:39:01,730
Anyway, you don't live
just for yourself!

584
00:39:01,780 --> 00:39:04,350
What about your sister,
your father, your little son?

585
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:06,440
They are a part of myself.

586
00:39:07,271 --> 00:39:09,630
All right, I concede,
one can't avoid the world entirely,

587
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:10,910
but I do my best.

588
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:13,880
I look after my estate,
I take care of my sister and my son,

589
00:39:14,470 --> 00:39:16,492
I serve in the local militia
with my father.

590
00:39:16,542 --> 00:39:18,999
- And that is enough for me.
- You won't go back to the army?

591
00:39:19,049 --> 00:39:21,600
After Austerlitz? No, thanks.

592
00:39:22,061 --> 00:39:25,181
The pursuit of military glory
disgusts me now.

593
00:39:26,398 --> 00:39:28,310
And besides,
Kutuzov was our last good man,

594
00:39:28,360 --> 00:39:29,680
and now the Tsar's demoted him.

595
00:39:29,730 --> 00:39:31,521
And what about yourself?

596
00:39:31,571 --> 00:39:34,962
You have so much to give.
Marry again, why not?

597
00:39:35,012 --> 00:39:37,923
And make some
other poor girl unhappy?

598
00:39:37,973 --> 00:39:41,453
I'm surprised to hear you
recommend marriage, Pierre.

599
00:39:42,781 --> 00:39:45,787
We neither of us distinguished
ourselves there, did we?

600
00:39:53,353 --> 00:39:55,778
Look, I must say this to you.
We've had all these conversations

601
00:39:55,828 --> 00:39:57,811
and you've been talking
as if your life is over,

602
00:39:57,861 --> 00:40:00,021
but you're a young man still.

603
00:40:00,401 --> 00:40:02,632
You know, so many good things
can happen for you.

604
00:40:02,682 --> 00:40:05,393
Since I became a Mason
and started to live a good life,

605
00:40:05,443 --> 00:40:07,363
I feel capable of anything!

606
00:40:07,947 --> 00:40:10,000
We must live.

607
00:40:10,330 --> 00:40:12,200
You know, we must love.

608
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:15,332
And we must believe that

609
00:40:15,770 --> 00:40:18,360
that there's more to it all than
our lives on this scrap of earth.

610
00:40:18,410 --> 00:40:21,420
There's something else out there -
it is true, Andrei.

611
00:40:22,898 --> 00:40:24,498
You must believe it.

612
00:40:32,146 --> 00:40:34,266
Yes, if only it were so.

613
00:40:41,054 --> 00:40:45,214
Pierre, I'd like you to meet my son.

614
00:40:45,659 --> 00:40:49,300
And it must be years since my father
and my sister set eyes on you.

615
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:52,147
Can you spare the time?

616
00:40:52,197 --> 00:40:54,597
For you,
I've all the time in the world.

617
00:41:07,212 --> 00:41:09,292
MAN WHISPERS: He's a funny fish.

618
00:41:11,840 --> 00:41:13,963
BOY WHISPERS: He makes a funny face!

619
00:41:14,013 --> 00:41:15,733
[LAUGHS]

620
00:41:16,272 --> 00:41:18,412
How do you find Andrei?

621
00:41:19,321 --> 00:41:21,601
He worries me so much.

622
00:41:22,150 --> 00:41:23,812
Today, he's merry and lively,

623
00:41:23,862 --> 00:41:26,053
but that's just your effect on him.

624
00:41:26,103 --> 00:41:27,760
He is unhappy.

625
00:41:29,312 --> 00:41:31,680
But it's not as though
he's doing nothing, Princess.

626
00:41:31,730 --> 00:41:32,770
I know.

627
00:41:34,196 --> 00:41:36,036
He does everything well.

628
00:41:38,722 --> 00:41:41,442
But it's as if the soul
has gone out of him.

629
00:41:43,882 --> 00:41:45,020
[DOOR OPENS]

630
00:41:45,070 --> 00:41:46,550
My father's home.

631
00:41:47,186 --> 00:41:49,560
Oh! Do you want to go
and say hello to your grandfather?

632
00:42:03,024 --> 00:42:04,716
'No more war?'

633
00:42:04,766 --> 00:42:07,552
This peace treaty with France
won't last. Mark my words,

634
00:42:07,602 --> 00:42:09,830
we'll be fighting Napoleon again
before you're much older!

635
00:42:09,880 --> 00:42:13,550
No, sir! We must believe
the man is capable of evolving.

636
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,120
Evolving?

637
00:42:15,170 --> 00:42:16,823
Men don't change!

638
00:42:16,873 --> 00:42:19,472
If you could drain the blood
from their veins and put in water,

639
00:42:19,522 --> 00:42:21,322
there might be no war!

640
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:24,049
You're talking
old women's nonsense, sir,

641
00:42:24,099 --> 00:42:28,218
but I'm happy to see that there are
still a few idealists left on Earth.

642
00:42:30,025 --> 00:42:31,983
I want you to go to Otradnoe.

643
00:42:32,033 --> 00:42:33,960
The marshal there, Count Rostov,

644
00:42:34,010 --> 00:42:36,983
has failed to produce
half the men required of him.

645
00:42:37,033 --> 00:42:38,670
The army still needs
to be maintained,

646
00:42:38,720 --> 00:42:41,233
even in this time
of so-called peace.

647
00:42:41,283 --> 00:42:43,877
Rostov needs someone
to ginger him up a bit.

648
00:42:43,927 --> 00:42:45,744
- Do you know the man, at all?
- No, I don't.

649
00:42:45,794 --> 00:42:46,753
I do.

650
00:42:46,803 --> 00:42:50,880
He's a very good man.
Not practical, I suppose,

651
00:42:51,395 --> 00:42:53,243
but who am I to talk of such things?

652
00:42:53,293 --> 00:42:56,190
I'm very fond of him.
The whole family are delightful.

653
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:59,160
Well, there you are. You can
mix business with pleasure!

654
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,760
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

655
00:43:23,149 --> 00:43:25,429
[PIANO PLAYS]

656
00:43:26,931 --> 00:43:29,190
Do tell your father
that I shall do my very best to

657
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:32,510
make my contribution to the militia.
I've been very lax.

658
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:35,750
Do you know, I moved the family
to the country to save money,

659
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:37,911
but somehow, I've been
doing more entertaining here

660
00:43:37,961 --> 00:43:41,457
than I ever did in Moscow - hunts,
theatricals, dinners, musicians,

661
00:43:41,507 --> 00:43:42,597
endless guests coming to stay...

662
00:43:42,647 --> 00:43:44,274
Well, I shan't be
any further burden to you...

663
00:43:44,324 --> 00:43:46,493
Oh, no, no, no, my dear fellow,
I didn't mean you.

664
00:43:46,543 --> 00:43:48,806
Of course, you must stay the night.

665
00:43:48,856 --> 00:43:51,376
And as long as you wish!

666
00:43:52,436 --> 00:43:54,574
And you needn't be talking
to boring old men like me,

667
00:43:54,624 --> 00:43:57,636
I've seen you looking
at those lovely girls.

668
00:43:57,686 --> 00:44:01,320
Natasha! Stop that, my darling,
and come over here.

669
00:44:06,406 --> 00:44:08,356
My daughter, Natalia.

670
00:44:08,406 --> 00:44:11,106
Natasha, this is
Prince Andrei Bolkonsky,

671
00:44:11,156 --> 00:44:13,580
one of the great heroes
of Austerlitz.

672
00:44:13,630 --> 00:44:16,030
I'm happy to make
your acquaintance, sir.

673
00:44:20,069 --> 00:44:22,359
I think I saw you before, didn't I?

674
00:44:23,109 --> 00:44:24,334
Yes.

675
00:44:25,162 --> 00:44:27,280
Yes, you looked at me so severely!

676
00:44:27,896 --> 00:44:30,113
No, not at all. Not severely.

677
00:44:30,163 --> 00:44:31,434
At least, I hope not.

678
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:36,230
Go and take him away and talk to him,
Natasha. He's had enough of me.

679
00:44:36,280 --> 00:44:37,800
[SHE LAUGHS]

680
00:44:45,602 --> 00:44:48,292
Are you the Prince Andrei
that Pierre Bezukhov talks about?

681
00:44:48,342 --> 00:44:49,782
He is my greatest friend.

682
00:44:51,462 --> 00:44:55,020
He loves you very dearly.
I think you're his hero.

683
00:44:56,753 --> 00:44:58,433
Have you seen him lately?

684
00:44:58,607 --> 00:45:01,376
He's had so much trouble, I think,
and none of it his fault.

685
00:45:01,426 --> 00:45:03,815
I saw him just before I came here.

686
00:45:04,214 --> 00:45:07,240
I believe he's put his sorrows
behind him now -

687
00:45:07,636 --> 00:45:11,940
he's full of great plans
and love for his fellow man.

688
00:45:12,385 --> 00:45:15,880
Yes. Yes, that's just like him.

689
00:45:16,174 --> 00:45:17,960
I so want him to be happy.

690
00:45:19,400 --> 00:45:20,700
Like you.

691
00:45:22,043 --> 00:45:25,280
You seem to have
the gift of happiness.

692
00:45:27,808 --> 00:45:29,558
Don't we all have it?

693
00:45:29,859 --> 00:45:31,520
Somewhere within us?

694
00:45:45,557 --> 00:45:48,757
NATASHA: Come on, please?
One more time!

695
00:45:49,046 --> 00:45:52,086
SONYA: Yes, all right, but then
I'm blowing the candles out.

696
00:45:55,267 --> 00:45:57,467
[NATASHA AND SONYA SING]

697
00:46:40,011 --> 00:46:41,781
That's it - I'm going to sleep now.

698
00:46:41,831 --> 00:46:44,187
Oh, Sonya, how can you sleep?

699
00:46:44,237 --> 00:46:47,080
I feel as if I'm going to
stay awake till dawn.

700
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:49,898
Look at that lovely moon.

701
00:46:50,319 --> 00:46:53,600
I don't think it's the moon
that's keeping you awake.

702
00:46:54,030 --> 00:46:55,470
What, then?

703
00:46:57,562 --> 00:46:59,566
Do you like him very much?

704
00:46:59,616 --> 00:47:01,047
More than Boris?

705
00:47:01,097 --> 00:47:03,057
Yes, much more.

706
00:47:04,351 --> 00:47:06,434
There's something
so sad about him,

707
00:47:06,484 --> 00:47:08,600
and that frightens me a little.

708
00:47:09,124 --> 00:47:11,106
But he's going away,
and we're leaving for Petersburg -

709
00:47:11,156 --> 00:47:13,256
I don't suppose
I'll ever see him again.

710
00:47:14,741 --> 00:47:17,105
Oh, Sonya, I wish
I could fly away.

711
00:47:17,155 --> 00:47:20,339
Shall I try?
Would the air carry me?

712
00:47:20,389 --> 00:47:22,310
Don't be a fool!

713
00:47:22,360 --> 00:47:26,580
- Come to bed now.
- Oh, if you insist.

714
00:48:08,667 --> 00:48:10,147
[DOG BARKS]

715
00:48:15,142 --> 00:48:19,475
I understand you have made
a great effort to change your life.

716
00:48:19,525 --> 00:48:21,671
That's very commendable.

717
00:48:21,721 --> 00:48:23,882
How do you feel about yourself?

718
00:48:23,932 --> 00:48:27,070
Well, I can look at
myself without disgust now.

719
00:48:27,120 --> 00:48:28,196
But...

720
00:48:29,268 --> 00:48:30,809
still not happy.

721
00:48:32,342 --> 00:48:34,168
Not at all.

722
00:48:34,551 --> 00:48:37,590
I sleep badly,
I wake with fearful thoughts.

723
00:48:39,330 --> 00:48:41,210
What's the matter with me?

724
00:48:44,033 --> 00:48:48,479
Perhaps you are changing your world,

725
00:48:48,714 --> 00:48:50,754
and forgetting to change yourself.

726
00:48:53,077 --> 00:48:57,077
Do you try to forgive
those who have wounded you?

727
00:49:00,225 --> 00:49:04,045
"My dear Helene, I believe we should
resume married life together,

728
00:49:04,095 --> 00:49:05,855
"if that is agreeable to you."

729
00:49:08,998 --> 00:49:11,658
"I ask you to forgive me
for hurting your feelings,

730
00:49:11,708 --> 00:49:13,580
"and for any damage
to your reputation

731
00:49:13,630 --> 00:49:15,627
"that my conduct may have caused."

732
00:49:15,677 --> 00:49:17,390
Thank you, dear Pierre.

733
00:49:17,440 --> 00:49:21,840
"I am a better person now, I hope,
than I was when we last spoke."

734
00:49:22,369 --> 00:49:24,760
I can't believe you're back
with Bezukhov.

735
00:49:27,682 --> 00:49:31,842
No need to sound so shocked.
It makes perfect sense.

736
00:49:32,637 --> 00:49:35,345
We're not sharing a bed,
it's just for appearance's sake.

737
00:49:35,395 --> 00:49:36,784
So, nothing needs to change.

738
00:49:36,834 --> 00:49:38,315
Come back to bed.

739
00:49:38,365 --> 00:49:40,431
No, I've got too much on
this morning.

740
00:49:40,481 --> 00:49:42,275
Did you know the Rostovs
are back in town?

741
00:49:42,325 --> 00:49:43,954
I had heard, yes.

742
00:49:44,004 --> 00:49:46,970
Aren't you supposed to be engaged
to the daughter?

743
00:49:47,020 --> 00:49:49,244
That was just a childish thing.

744
00:49:49,294 --> 00:49:50,734
Does she know that?

745
00:49:50,784 --> 00:49:52,039
I should make it clear
if I were you -

746
00:49:52,089 --> 00:49:54,455
you can't afford to be engaged
to a girl with no money.

747
00:49:54,505 --> 00:49:56,728
You're not jealous, by any chance,
are you?

748
00:49:56,778 --> 00:49:58,178
Me? Jealous?

749
00:49:58,528 --> 00:50:00,386
Of the little Rostov girl?

750
00:50:00,436 --> 00:50:02,587
You're very sweet.

751
00:50:02,637 --> 00:50:04,579
You can see yourself out.

752
00:50:04,629 --> 00:50:06,206
Wait!

753
00:50:06,256 --> 00:50:08,766
I'll see you at the Tsar's ball?

754
00:50:08,816 --> 00:50:11,017
Well, you shall see me,
but you're not to talk to me,

755
00:50:11,067 --> 00:50:12,778
much less touch me.

756
00:50:12,828 --> 00:50:15,232
I shall be otherwise engaged,
and you need to find yourself

757
00:50:15,282 --> 00:50:17,662
a pretty little heiress
to charm out of her petticoat.

758
00:50:17,712 --> 00:50:20,573
- Think you can do that?
- I don't want to do that.

759
00:50:20,623 --> 00:50:21,945
I want you.

760
00:50:21,995 --> 00:50:23,275
Sweet boy.

761
00:50:30,430 --> 00:50:32,710
[DOOR OPENS]

762
00:50:43,323 --> 00:50:45,089
I'm so nervous!

763
00:50:45,729 --> 00:50:48,440
I've been awake for hours, thinking
about the Tsar's ball tonight.

764
00:50:48,490 --> 00:50:52,570
Oh, but you've got nothing to be
nervous about.

765
00:50:52,866 --> 00:50:57,306
It is important, my darling,
for you and for Sonya -

766
00:50:57,836 --> 00:51:01,312
the first time you'll be seen
in Petersburg society.

767
00:51:01,362 --> 00:51:04,082
Everyone's eyes will be on you.

768
00:51:05,577 --> 00:51:07,328
So, keep a clear head,

769
00:51:07,378 --> 00:51:10,338
and don't fall for the first boy
who asks you to dance.

770
00:51:11,467 --> 00:51:13,947
- Do you think he might be there?
- Who?

771
00:51:14,795 --> 00:51:17,557
[SHE LAUGHS]
You know, Mamma!

772
00:51:17,607 --> 00:51:19,640
Prince Andrei Bolkonsky.

773
00:51:20,280 --> 00:51:23,901
If God wills it, he'll be there,

774
00:51:23,951 --> 00:51:25,871
and you'll dance with him.

775
00:51:26,453 --> 00:51:29,613
Now, close your eyes.

776
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:40,270
[SHE SINGS A LULLABY]

777
00:51:40,320 --> 00:51:43,920
[LULLABY MERGES INTO BALLROOM MUSIC]

778
00:52:08,966 --> 00:52:11,006
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

779
00:52:21,189 --> 00:52:23,820
Look at those two. Ah!

780
00:52:23,870 --> 00:52:25,550
Charmantes!

781
00:52:27,254 --> 00:52:29,359
There's so many French here.

782
00:52:29,409 --> 00:52:32,368
- As if nothing ever changed.
- It won't last.

783
00:52:32,418 --> 00:52:35,328
Napoleon won't be able to resist
the temptation to invade Russia

784
00:52:35,378 --> 00:52:38,642
- for much longer.
- Oh! Bilibin, don't say that.

785
00:52:38,692 --> 00:52:41,590
Well, it's his nature. He's like
the scorpion - he has to sting,

786
00:52:41,640 --> 00:52:43,311
he can't help it.

787
00:52:43,361 --> 00:52:46,161
Ah! The Queen of Petersburg!

788
00:52:47,560 --> 00:52:49,880
His Imperial Majesty, The Tsar.

789
00:53:31,930 --> 00:53:33,593
- Old friend!
- Pierre!

790
00:53:33,643 --> 00:53:35,190
How are you?

791
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:36,977
I'm very well.

792
00:53:37,027 --> 00:53:40,368
Yes - I see something's changed
in you.

793
00:53:40,418 --> 00:53:43,209
I keep hearing reports you're
making waves in the court circles,

794
00:53:43,259 --> 00:53:44,899
reforming the army.

795
00:53:45,358 --> 00:53:47,958
The old spark's burning bright
again, isn't it?

796
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:50,723
You could put it like that.

797
00:53:50,773 --> 00:53:52,973
And what about you?

798
00:53:54,040 --> 00:53:55,305
Oh,

799
00:53:56,329 --> 00:54:01,000
you don't want to hear about me.
I'm, I'm very happy to see you again.

800
00:54:15,785 --> 00:54:17,385
May I have this dance?

801
00:54:27,844 --> 00:54:30,284
- May I take your hand for this dance?
- Of course.

802
00:54:48,127 --> 00:54:49,727
Countess Rostova.

803
00:54:50,776 --> 00:54:54,736
May I request the pleasure of
a dance with your daughter, Natalia?

804
00:54:54,786 --> 00:54:57,546
Of course! She'll be delighted.

805
00:55:09,612 --> 00:55:12,652
[MUSIC STARTS]

806
00:56:12,831 --> 00:56:16,751
[PIANO MUSIC PLAYS]

807
00:56:52,172 --> 00:56:53,372
It's him!

808
00:57:08,320 --> 00:57:10,920
[LAUGHTER AND CHATTER]

809
00:57:20,514 --> 00:57:23,314
[THEY LAUGH]

810
00:57:39,327 --> 00:57:43,939
I had no idea, Pierre. I've never
experienced anything like it before.

811
00:57:43,989 --> 00:57:45,041
Like what, exactly?

812
00:57:45,091 --> 00:57:46,830
I'm in love, my friend!

813
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:49,750
Yes. Yes, with Natasha Rostova, yes?

814
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:54,519
Yes, who else? I feel like I've
never been properly alive before.

815
00:57:54,569 --> 00:57:57,790
I feel I can't live without her,
Pierre!

816
00:57:57,840 --> 00:58:00,510
But could she love me?
Might she think I'm too old.

817
00:58:00,560 --> 00:58:02,920
I am too old! What do you think?

818
00:58:04,440 --> 00:58:05,880
Why don't you speak?

819
00:58:08,145 --> 00:58:10,325
The girl is a treasure, Andrei.

820
00:58:11,306 --> 00:58:13,946
She's one of a kind.
She's a treasure.

821
00:58:15,954 --> 00:58:19,099
Look, if you truly love her,
don't hesitate,

822
00:58:19,149 --> 00:58:21,545
don't think about it.
Follow your heart, marry her.

823
00:58:21,595 --> 00:58:23,807
Marry her tomorrow -
you'll never regret it!

824
00:58:23,857 --> 00:58:25,783
- But could she love me, Pierre?
- She loves you all right.

825
00:58:25,833 --> 00:58:28,973
- She hardly knows me...
- She loves you! I know it! All right?

826
00:58:29,980 --> 00:58:33,020
I could see it in her face
when she was dancing with you.

827
00:58:33,374 --> 00:58:35,074
I've never seen her
look like that before,

828
00:58:35,124 --> 00:58:37,364
and I've known her
since she was a child.

829
00:58:38,292 --> 00:58:40,092
She loves you, Andrei.

830
00:58:41,039 --> 00:58:43,119
And you're
the luckiest man on Earth.

831
00:58:44,737 --> 00:58:47,037
So, what are you doing talking
to me?

832
00:58:47,408 --> 00:58:48,808
Go to her!

833
00:58:50,215 --> 00:58:52,832
Go to her, don't let her get away.

834
00:58:52,882 --> 00:58:54,482
Propose to her.

835
00:58:57,903 --> 00:58:59,360
I will.

836
00:59:10,852 --> 00:59:12,372
[DOOR CLOSES]

